      • getLocalFilename

        public String getLocalFilename(int blockIndex)
                        throws IOException
        Deprecated. 
        Returns the local filename for the block if that file exists on the local file system. This is an alpha power-api feature for applications that want short-circuit-read files directly. There is no guarantee that the file still exists after this call returns, as Tachyon may evict blocks from memory at any time.
        Parameters:
        blockIndex - The index of the block in the file
        Returns:
        filename on local file system or null if file not present on local file system
        Throws:
        IOException - if the underlying file does not exist or its metadata is corrupted
